      <h1>Frequently Asked Questions (FAQ)</h1>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-question">Q: How do I search for a movie?</div>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          A: Simply type the movie title into the search bar on the homepage and
          click the "Search" button.
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-question">Q: Where does the movie data come from?</div>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          A: All movie data, including posters and descriptions, is retrieved
          from The Movie Database (TMDB) API.
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-question">Q: Is this application free to use?</div>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          A: Yes, this application is completely free to use for personal movie
          searching.
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-question">Q: Can I contribute to this project?</div>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          A: This is a demonstration project. For real-world projects,
          contributions are often welcome via GitHub.
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-question">Q: What if I can't find a movie?</div>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          A: Ensure your spelling is correct. If the movie is very new or
          obscure, it might not yet be in the TMDB database.
        </div>
      </div>
